  <section xml:id="grading">
    <title>Course Requirements and Grading</title>
    <!--Edit this example as necessary for your course.-->
    <p>
      Final grades will be determined using the following assignment categories (descriptions below):
    </p>
    <tabular>
      <row header="yes">
        <cell>Assignment Category</cell> <cell>Weight</cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>MyLab Online Homework </cell> <cell>15%</cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>Weekly Quizzes (will drop lowest 2 quiz scores) </cell> <cell>15%</cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>Three Midterm Exams</cell> <cell>16% each</cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>Cumulative Final Exam</cell> <cell>22%</cell>
      </row>
    </tabular>
    <p>
      Grading Scale
    </p>
    <tabular>
      <row header="yes">
        <cell>Letter Grade</cell><cell>Point Range (<m>P</m>)</cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>A </cell><cell><m>P &gt;93</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>A-</cell><cell><m>90\leq P &lt; 93</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>B+</cell><cell><m>87\leq P &lt; 90</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>B</cell><cell><m>83\leq P &lt; 87</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>B-</cell><cell><m>80\leq P &lt; 83</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>C+</cell><cell><m>77\leq P &lt; 80</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>C</cell><cell><m>73\leq P &lt; 77</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>C-</cell><cell><m>70\leq P &lt; 73</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>D+</cell><cell><m>67\leq P &lt; 70</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>D</cell><cell><m>63\leq P &lt; 67</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>D-</cell><cell><m>60\leq P &lt; 63</m></cell>
      </row>
      <row>
        <cell>F</cell><cell><m> P &lt; 60</m></cell>
      </row>
    </tabular>

  
  <paragraphs xml:id="webwork">
    <title>MyLab</title>
    <p>
     Homework will be assigned and completed via MyLab.  This is integrated within Canvas.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      It is important to keep on pace, so homework will typically be due before the next class meeting.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs xml:id="weekly-activities">
    <title>Weekly Quizzes</title>
    <p>
      There will be at least one quiz each non-exam week.  These may be unannounced.  Questions on the quizzes will be similar to those on the homework.  If you can answer the homework questions, you will be able to answer the quiz questions. Keep in mind that no electronic devices are allowed during quizzes.

    </p>

    <p>
      
      
      To account for missed quizzes due to unforseen circumstances, I will drop the lowest 2 scores at the end of the term.  No make-up quizzes.
      
    </p>
    
    
  </paragraphs>
<!--
  <paragraphs xml:id="engagement">
    <title>Engagement</title>
    <p>
      Once a week (generally Tuesdays) we will focus more on group work. Your weekly engagement score will be based on being present and actively engaged for the duration of these class periods. The lowest two engagement scores will be dropped at the end of the term to account for unexpected circumstances that prevent attendance. 
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
-->

  <paragraphs xml:id="midterm-exams">
    <title>Midterm Exams</title>
    <p>
      There will be three midterm exams: 
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Monday, 21-September
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Wednesday, 21-October
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Friday, 20-November (this is the Friday before break, please do no plan to leave early)
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs xml:id="final">
    <title>Cumulative Final Exam</title>
    <p>
      Your cumulative final exam will be Tuesday, 8-December, from 7:30-9:30am. 
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
</section>